The paper presents a system for gesture recognition using WiFi signals around a mobile device. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it involves interaction between humans and technology. The system also involves signal processing and machine learning techniques for gesture recognition, which could fall under the categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), multimedia (cs.MM), and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses challenges related to signal processing and noise reduction, which could fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
